## Comprehensive Psychology Note

**ID:** 6  
**Type IDs:** 1,2  
**Category IDs:** 1,2,3  

### Description

This note template covers many aspects of client presentation, using the following titles: Current Presentation, Past Medical & Psychiatric History, Mental Status Examination, Session Content, Obstacles, Setbacks and Progress, Interventions, Risk Assessment and Management, Session Summary, Next Steps

### Prompt

### Current Presentation:

* [Describe client's current presentation or presenting complaint or primary reason for seeking therapy this visit, how long the issue(s) have been occurring, etc] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes otherwise leave blank)
* Severity/Impact: [describe current impact on functioning, for example, impact on work/school/activities of daily life, etc] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual note, otherwise leave blank)

### Past Medical & Psychiatric History:

* Psychiatric Diagnoses: [Details of any psychiatric diagnoses] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes otherwise leave blank)
* Medical history: [Details of any recent medical issues] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes otherwise leave blank)
* Treatments / Hospitalisations: [Details of any recent interventions or treatments, including hospitalisations if any] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes otherwise leave blank)
* Current Medications: [List current medications, including details such as dose and frequency] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes otherwise leave blank. If there is no mention of medication in the transcript, leave blank.)
* Recent Substance Use: [Details of any recent substance use, including type, frequency, and duration] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)

### Mental Status Examination:

* Behaviour: [Observe the client's activity level, interaction with their surroundings, and any unique or notable behaviors (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank).]
* Speech: [If the pace of speech was fast or slow for the speaker who is the client, note the pace of speech for the client, where a “normal pace of speech” is between 130 and 200 words per minute, “fast pace of speech” is defined as 201 words per minute or over, and “slow pace of speech” is defined as less than 129 words per minute. Only include a note on the pace of speech if it is fast or slow, if it is normal, do not include it in the note]
* Mood: [Record the client's self-described emotional state, using their own words if possible (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank).]
* Affect: [Describe the range and appropriateness of the client's emotional response during the examination, noting any discrepancies with the stated mood (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank).]
* Thoughts: [Assess the client's thought process and thought content, noting any distortions, delusions, or preoccupations (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank).]
* Perceptions: [Note any reported hallucinations or sensory misinterpretations, specifying type and impact on the client (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank).]
* Cognition: [Describe the client's memory, orientation to time/place/person, concentration, and comprehension (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank).]
* Insight: [Describe the client's understanding of their own condition and symptoms, noting any lack of awareness or denial (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank).]
* Judgment: [Describe the client's decision-making ability and understanding of the consequences of their actions (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank).]

### Session Content:

* [Describe details of other relevant discussions with client during the session] (use as many bullet points as needed to capture all the details discussed; only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)
* [Describe details of any life events, milestones, or circumstances that have occurred or are upcoming for the client] (use as many bullet points as needed to capture all the details discussed)
* [List key relationships the client has including names and key details or interactions] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes otherwise leave blank)

### Goals:

* [Describe in detail any goals that were discussed, including if any new objectives, desires or things to work on were discussed, or if existing goals were reviewed. When available, describe SMART goals and quote specific aims.] (use as many bullet points as needed to capture all the details discussed; only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)
* [Note anything that the therapist asked the client to do during the week, or before the next session. Note anything the therapist said the client could try. Record if the client agreed to any tasks between sessions] (use as many bullet points as needed to capture all the details discussed; only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)

### Obstacles, Setbacks and Progress:

* [Describe in detail the progress achieved by client towards each therapy goal/objective] (use as many bullet points as needed to capture all the details discussed; only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)
* [Describe in detail the setbacks and obstacles to progress for each therapy goal/objective] (use as many bullet points as needed to capture all the details discussed; only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)

### Interventions:

* [Describe details of specific therapeutic techniques and interventions used or to be used] (use as many bullet points as needed to capture all the details discussed) (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)
* [Describe any ideas, concepts or frameworks that were introduced, or the content of any handouts or use of whiteboard) (use as many bullet points as needed to capture all the details discussed) (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)

### Risk Assessment and Management:

* Suicidal Ideation: [describe any history of suicidal ideation, attempts, plans in detail] (if current suicidal thoughts or behaviours are present, highlight text in red) (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)
* Homicidal Ideation: [Describe any homicidal ideation] (if past or current homicidal thoughts or behaviours are mentioned, highlight text in red) (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise exclude this section)
* Self-harm: [Detail any history of self-harm] (if current self-harm is present, highlight text in red) (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)
* Violence & Aggression: [Describe any recent or past incidents of violence or aggression] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)
* Addictive Behaviours: [Detail any recent or past addictive behaviours, e.g., illicit drugs, gambling] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)
* Risk-taking/Impulsivity: [Describe any risk-taking behaviors or impulsivity] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)
* Management Plan: [Describe strategy or steps taken to manage suicidal ideation / homicidal ideation / self-harm / violence & aggression / substance use / risk-taking behaviour (if applicable)] (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)

### Session Summary:

[Summarise client's progress in a paragraph with emphasis on current status, risk assessment and management, interventions, progress towards achieving therapy goals/objectives, setbacks, obstacles]

### Next Steps:

* Next Session: [mention date and time of next session, mention any plans about next session (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)]
* Assigned Homework: [Any tasks or activities assigned to the client (only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)]

