## ADOS-2 Module 1 Assessment Summary

**ID:** 21255  
**Type IDs:** 3  
**Category IDs:** 1  

### Description

A comprehensive observational summary template for the Autism Diagnostic Observation Schedule, Second Edition (ADOS-2) Module 1. This module is designed for children 31 months and older who do not consistently use phrase speech. The template captures behavioural observations across communication, social interaction, play, and restricted/repetitive behaviours during the standardised assessment activities, supporting diagnostic formulation using neurodiversity-affirming language balanced with standardised clinical terminology. It is recommended that clinicians include their behavioural observations of the client as a note or added context, prior to generating the summary.

### Prompt

(The template below is designed for psychologists administering the Autism Diagnostic Observation Schedule, Second Edition, also known as the ADOS-2, Module 1 assessment. This is a standardised, semi-structured, play-based observational assessment designed to evaluate social communication, reciprocal social interaction, play, and restricted/repetitive behaviours in children who do not consistently use phrase speech. Using the transcript, contextual notes, and observations from the session, you will generate a detailed summary of behavioural observations made during the standardised assessment activities. The summary should capture the child's presentation, behaviours across all domains, and clinical impressions in a way that balances neurodiversity-affirming language with standardised ADOS-2 terminology. Use the DSM-5-TR criteria and ADOS-2 framework when describing observations. Organise the summary under the following headings.)

<br>
#### ADOS-2 Module 1


Algorithm:

[Specify: Few to No Words / Some Words. If unknown, print: “Unable to determine.”]

Child Information:

* Child Name: [Print the client’s first and last name.]
* Date of Birth: [Print the client’s date of birth in Day Month, Year format.]
* Chronological Age: [Print the client’s age on the day of the assessment in Years, Months format.]
* Date of Assessment: [Print the date of the assessment in Day Month, Year format.]

Attendance:

[CHILD NAME] attended the session with [CAREGIVER(S)].

Initial Presentation:

[Describe the child's presentation on arrival, e.g., calm / curious / anxious / distressed / engaged / withdrawn / tired. Describe engagement with the clinician on entry, e.g., approached readily / stayed close to caregiver / avoided eye contact / needed encouragement to enter the assessment room. (If unable to make a judgment based on the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, print: “Unable to determine from available information.”)]

BEHAVIOURAL OBSERVATIONS DURING ADOS-2 MODULE 1

**LANGUAGE AND COMMUNICATION**

**Overall Expressive Language Level:**

[Describe the child's expressive language, e.g., nonverbal / single words only / occasional short phrases / primarily jargon / echolalia present / use of communicative sounds without words. (If unable to make a judgment based on the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, print: “Unable to determine from available information.”)]

**Frequency of Spontaneous Vocalisations Directed to Others:**

[Describe how often the child directed vocalisations, sounds, or words toward others, e.g., frequent spontaneous vocalisations / occasional vocalisations when motivated / rare or no vocalisations directed to others. (If unable to make a judgment based on the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, print: “Unable to determine from available information.”)]

**Intonation of Vocalisations or Verbalisations:**

[Describe the quality and variation of intonation by the child, e.g., varied and appropriate intonation / limited prosodic variation / unusual or flat intonation / stereotyped or repetitive vocalisations. (If unable to make a judgment based on the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, print: “Unable to determine from available information.”)]

**Immediate Echolalia:**

[Describe any immediate repetition of words or phrases by the child, e.g., no echolalia observed / occasional echolalia / frequent immediate repetition of clinician's speech. (If unable to make a judgment based on the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, print: “Unable to determine from available information.”)]

**Stereotyped / Idiosyncratic Use of Words or Phrases:**

