**Risk and Safety:**

[If no concerns, print: "No immediate safety concerns were identified during today's assessment."]

[If concerns present: Briefly describe any risk behaviours, safety concerns, elopement attempts, aggression, or self-injurious behaviours, and note actions taken or still to be taken. (If unable to make a judgment based on the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, print: “Unable to determine from available information.”)]

**Child's Engagement:**

[Describe the child's apparent willingness to participate, response to breaks and boundaries, and overall tolerance of the assessment process, e.g., tolerated assessment well overall / showed some distress but was able to continue with breaks / required shortened session due to distress. (If unable to make a judgment based on the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, print: “Unable to determine from available information.”)]

