## Applied Behaviour Analysis (ABA) Session Note

**ID:** 19169  
**Type IDs:** 1,2  
**Category IDs:** 1,3,4  

### Description

For therapists using Applied Behaviour Analysis (ABA) with clients who have autism spectrum disorder, intellectual disabilities, or other developmental disabilities. This template summarises both direct therapy sessions with individual clients and parent/caregiver training sessions.

### Prompt

(The template below is designed to be used by Applied Behaviour Analysis (ABA) therapists, behaviour analysts, and behaviour technicians working with clients across the lifespan using Applied Behaviour Analysis. Using the transcript from the session, you will generate a detailed summary from an ABA perspective.)

(CRITICAL INSTRUCTION: First, determine the session type. If the session involved direct work with the client (with or without caregiver present), use SECTION A: DIRECT THERAPY SESSION. If the session was primarily focused on training parents/caregivers without the client present or with minimal client involvement, use SECTION B: PARENT/CAREGIVER TRAINING SESSION. Only complete the section that matches the session type. Do not complete both sections for a single session.)

**SECTION A: DIRECT THERAPY SESSION**

(Complete this section only if the session involved direct therapeutic work with the client.)

**Session Information:**

[Document the following: Date and time of session (start and end time), total duration, location of session (e.g., home, clinic, school, community), service type (e.g., 1:1 direct ABA therapy, group session), therapist/technician name and credentials, client name and age. Note if caregiver was present during session.]

**Client Presentation:**

[Describe the client's presentation at the start of the session, including affect, mood, engagement level, and any notable physical or emotional state. Note any changes from previous sessions. Document any relevant contextual factors (e.g., changes in medication, sleep, recent life events) that may impact the session. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Programs and Targets Addressed:**

[Describe the specific skill acquisition programs and/or behaviour reduction plans that were targeted during this session. For each program, briefly note the specific targets worked on. Include program names as they appear in the treatment plan (e.g., "Receptive Language: Following 1-step directions," "Social Skills: Initiating greetings," "Manding: Requesting preferred items using AAC device", etc.) (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Session Activities and Teaching Procedures:**

[Describe what occurred during the session and the teaching procedures used. Detail the ABA teaching methods employed (e.g., Discrete Trial Training/DTT, Natural Environment Teaching/NET, incidental teaching, task analysis, chaining, shaping, etc.). Note the structure of the session (e.g., structured table work, naturalistic play-based instruction, community-based instruction). Describe specific activities conducted and how they related to target programs. Include any modifications made to planned activities and the rationale for changes. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Data Collection Summary:**

(Create a list to present quantitative data collected during the session. Organise by program/target and include relevant metrics.)

<br>
* **Program/Target:** [Name of skill or behaviour]
* **Data Type:** [Specify: trial-by-trial, frequency, duration, percentage, interval recording, etc.]
* **Performance Summary:** [e.g., "8/10 correct responses (80% accuracy)", "Requested independently 5 times", "Tantrum duration: 3 minutes total across 2 occurrences"]
* **Prompt Level:** [If applicable, note prompting required: e.g., "Responded independently on 3/10 trials, required verbal prompt on 5/10 trials, required physical prompt on 2/10 trials"]
* **Comparison to Previous Session:** [Note trend: improving, maintaining, declining, variable]


[Repeat the above format for each program/target addressed in session. In the event that there is more than one program/target, be sure to leave a blank line space before each new program/target.]

[For behaviour reduction: Include ABC (Antecedent-Behaviour-Consequence) data if challenging behaviours occurred, documenting what happened before, the behaviour itself, and the consequence provided.]

**Prompting and Prompt Fading:**

[Describe the prompting strategies used during the session (e.g., verbal prompts, gestural prompts, model prompts, physical prompts, visual prompts, etc.). Note any progress with prompt fading or changes to the prompting hierarchy. Document the client's response to different prompt levels. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Reinforcement Strategies:**

[Describe the reinforcement strategies employed during the session. Note the reinforcement schedule used (e.g., continuous reinforcement, variable ratio, fixed ratio, token economy, etc.). Describe what reinforcers were effective (e.g., tangibles, edibles, praise, preferred activities, sensory items, tokens, etc.). Note any changes to reinforcement strategies and their effectiveness. Document any preference assessments conducted. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Challenging Behaviours:**

[If challenging behaviours occurred, document them objectively. Include frequency, duration, and/or intensity. Describe the antecedents (what happened immediately before), the behaviour itself (in observable, measurable terms), and consequences provided. Note any patterns observed. Document the effectiveness of behaviour intervention strategies implemented. If no challenging behaviours occurred, state this explicitly.]

**Barriers and Challenges:**

[Describe any barriers encountered during the session (e.g., environmental distractions, equipment issues, client illness, competing motivating operations, session interruptions, etc.). Note how barriers were addressed and their impact on session productivity. Include any environmental modifications made.]

**Client Response and Progress:**

[Describe how the client responded to interventions and teaching throughout the session. Note engagement level, motivation, attention span, and cooperation. Highlight any notable successes, breakthroughs, or "aha moments." Document any difficulties or barriers to learning observed. Describe the client's overall responsiveness to prompts, reinforcement, and error correction procedures.]

**Skill Generalisation and Maintenance:**

[Describe any evidence of skill generalisation (e.g., using skills in new settings, with different materials, or with different people). Document maintenance of previously mastered skills if assessed. Describe any strategies used to promote generalisation (e.g., varying materials, changing instructors, practicing in natural environments, etc.).]

**Caregiver Involvement:**

[If caregiver was present during the session, describe their involvement. Note any observations they shared, questions they asked, or concerns they raised. Document any informal coaching or guidance provided to the caregiver during the session. Note caregiver's understanding and implementation of strategies if they participated in activities with the client. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Clinical Decisions and Modifications:**

[Describe any clinical decisions made during the session. Document modifications to teaching procedures, prompting levels, reinforcement schedules, or mastery criteria. Explain the rationale for any changes made to programming. Note if any targets were mastered, put on maintenance, or discontinued. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Risk Assessment:**

[Describe any risk factors discussed or observed, such as self-harm, aggression toward others, elopement risk, or suicidal ideation. If current suicidal thoughts or behaviours are present, highlight this information. List protective factors that mitigate the risk. Document any safety plans in place or action plans implemented if risk is elevated. If no risk factors are present, state this explicitly.]

**Plan and Next Steps:**

[Describe any recommendations from the therapist made in today’s session. Note any programming changes stated by the therapist or caregiver (e.g., increasing difficulty, fading prompts, adjusting reinforcement, modifying behaviour intervention strategies, etc.). Identify areas requiring additional focus or senior clinician consultation, as stated by the therapist or caregiver. Describe any environmental modifications or material needs for upcoming sessions, as stated by the therapist or caregiver. Outline the preliminary plan for the next session, including which programs and targets will be prioritised, as stated by the therapist or caregiver. Note the planned date/time of the next session if established. Include any preparations needed for the next session (e.g., materials to gather, activities to plan, caregiver coordination, etc.), as stated by the therapist or the caregiver.]

**Session Summary:**

[Provide a concise summary of the session in less than four sentences. Include overall productivity of the session, key highlights of client progress or challenges, and primary focus moving forward.]

**SECTION B: PARENT/CAREGIVER TRAINING SESSION**

(Complete this section only if the session was primarily focused on training the parent/caregiver.)

**Session Information:**

[Document the following: Date and time of session (start and end time), total duration of session, location of session, service type (Parent/Caregiver Training), clinician name conducting the training, parent/caregiver name(s) and relationship to client, client name and age. Note if client was present during training or if training was conducted without client present.]

**Caregiver Presentation and Context:**

[Describe the caregiver's engagement level, receptiveness to training, and any relevant contextual information. Note any concerns, questions, or specific challenges the caregiver raised at the beginning of the session. Document the caregiver's emotional state and readiness to learn.]

**Training Goals and Objectives:**

[Describe the specific parent/caregiver training goals being addressed in this session as outlined in the treatment plan. Examples: "Caregiver will implement differential reinforcement of alternative behaviour (DRA) with 80% fidelity," "Parent will identify relevant antecedents for target behaviours with 80% accuracy," "Caregiver will implement prompting hierarchy for self-help skills with correct sequence." Note which goals were the primary focus of today's session. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Topics Covered and Content Delivered:**

[Describe the ABA principles, strategies, and techniques taught during the session. Include specific topics covered (e.g., understanding function of behaviour, implementing token economy system, using visual schedules, applying prompting strategies, conducting preference assessments, using specific behaviour management techniques, etc.). Note any educational materials provided (handouts, videos, visual aids, etc.). Describe how concepts were explained and whether real-life examples relevant to the family were used.]

**Training Methods and Demonstrations:**

[Describe how the training was delivered. Note if the clinician used explanation, modeling/demonstration, role-play, in-vivo coaching (coaching while caregiver interacts with client), video examples, or written materials. Describe any demonstrations provided by the therapist and what specific techniques were demonstrated. Document whether the training was didactic, interactive, or experiential.]

**Caregiver Practice and Implementation:**

[Describe what the caregiver practiced during the session. Document the caregiver's actual implementation of strategies with observable details. For example: "Parent practiced the 3-step prompting sequence (verbal cue → gestural prompt → physical guidance) during 5 opportunities for toothbrushing. Achieved 60% fidelity, requiring one verbal cue from clinician for correct prompt timing." Note the caregiver's fidelity to procedures using measurable data where possible (e.g., percentage of steps completed correctly, number of prompts required from therapist, etc.).]

**Caregiver Performance Data:**

(If applicable, present data on caregiver's implementation of strategies.)

<br>
* **Strategy/Skill Practiced:** [Name the specific ABA technique.]
* **Implementation Fidelity:** [e.g., "Implemented 7/10 steps correctly (70% fidelity)", "Provided reinforcement within 2 seconds on 4/5 opportunities".]
* **Areas of Strength:** [What the caregiver did well.]
* **Areas for Improvement:** [What needs additional practice or clarification.]
* **Prompts/Supports Provided by Clinician:** [Note coaching provided.]


[Repeat for each skill/strategy practiced. In the event that there is more than one strategy/skill, be sure to leave a blank line space before each new strategy/skill.]

**Connection to Client Treatment Plan:**

[Explicitly connect the caregiver training to the client's goals and current programming. Explain how the caregiver's implementation of these strategies will support the client's progress. Reference specific client behaviours or skills that will be impacted. Include brief data or observation about how improved caregiver implementation is affecting client outcomes if applicable (e.g., "Caregiver's improved use of reinforcement correlates with client's 15% increase in compliance over the past two weeks per session data"). (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Caregiver Understanding and Engagement:**

[Describe the caregiver's level of understanding of concepts taught. Note questions asked by the caregiver and answers provided. Describe the caregiver's engagement level and receptiveness to feedback. Document any concerns, resistance, or barriers to implementation raised by the caregiver. Note the caregiver's confidence level in implementing strategies independently.]

**Caregiver Goals Progress:**

[Review progress toward the caregiver's training goals outlined in the treatment plan. Note if goals were met, progressing, or require additional support. Document any updates needed to caregiver goals based on current performance and needs. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Barriers to Implementation:**

[Describe any barriers the caregiver identified or that were observed during the session. These may include: time constraints, other family members not implementing consistently, difficulty managing multiple children, emotional challenges, physical limitations, lack of materials/resources, competing demands. Document how these barriers were addressed during the session.]

**Problem-Solving and Collaboration:**

[Describe any collaborative problem-solving that occurred. Note how the therapist and caregiver worked together to address challenges or adapt strategies to fit the family's routine and lifestyle. Document any modifications made to strategies to increase feasibility for the family. Highlight examples of the caregiver contributing ideas or insights about their child.]

**Home Practice Plan and Assignments:**

[Detail the specific homework or practice assignments given to the caregiver by the therapist. Be explicit about what the therapist has advised the caregiver to do, when, and how often. Include:]

<br>
* **Strategy to Practice:** [Name the specific technique.]
* **Frequency/Schedule:** [e.g., "Practice during 3 mealtimes daily", "Use token board for 2 target behaviours throughout the day".]
* **Data Collection Required:** [e.g., "Record frequency of independently completed steps on provided data sheet", "Note times when strategy was used in caregiver journal".]
* **Materials Provided:** [List any materials given to support home implementation.]


[Include the rationale provided by the therapist for assignments and expected outcomes. Note any concerns the caregiver expressed about completing assignments.]

**Educational Materials and Resources Provided:**

[List all handouts, worksheets, written instructions, video links, apps, or other resources provided to the caregiver by the therapist. Include titles/descriptions of materials. Note if materials are in the caregiver's preferred language and at an appropriate comprehension level. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Clinical Observations and Reflections:**

[Describe the clinician's professional observations about the training session. Note the quality of the therapeutic relationship with the caregiver. Describe the therapist’s reflections on the effectiveness of teaching methods used. Identify any adjustments needed for future training sessions to better meet the caregiver's learning style or needs. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Risk Assessment:**

[Describe any risk factors discussed or observed, such as self-harm, aggression toward others, elopement risk, or suicidal ideation. If current suicidal thoughts or behaviours are present, highlight this information. List protective factors that mitigate the risk. Document any safety plans in place or action plans implemented if risk is elevated. If no risk factors are present, state this explicitly.]

**Next Steps:**

[Outline the preliminary agenda for the next parent/caregiver training session as agreed upon by the therapist and the caregiver. Note which goals will be targeted next. Specify the planned date/time of next training session. Include any preparations needed (materials to create, videos to review, etc.). Document the plan for following up on home practice. Note how progress will be monitored (e.g., caregiver will bring completed data sheets to next session, clinician will review video of caregiver implementation, follow-up phone call scheduled, etc.). Include any scheduled check-ins between now and the next training session. If applicable, note any discussion about coordination with other professionals involved in the client's care (e.g., speech therapist, occupational therapist, school team). Document any information shared about the client's progress or strategies that should be communicated to other team members. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Session Summary:**

[Provide a concise summary of the training session in less than four sentences. Include what was taught, how the caregiver responded, key outcomes, and the focus for continued caregiver development.]

