## DIR / Floortime Session Note

**ID:** 19186  
**Type IDs:** 1,2  
**Category IDs:** 1,3,4,5  

### Description

This template is designed for therapists working within the DIR/Floortime (Developmental, Individual-differences, Relationship-based) framework. It captures the play-based, relationship-centred approach used primarily with children who have autism spectrum disorder, developmental delays, or intellectual disabilities. The template focuses on the child's functional emotional developmental capacities (FEDCs), individual sensory and processing differences, and the therapeutic relationship.

### Prompt

(The template below is designed to be used by therapists working within a DIR/Floortime framework with child clients who present with developmental challenges including autism spectrum disorder, developmental delays, and intellectual or developmental disabilities. Using the transcript from the session or dictated note, you will generate a detailed summary of the session from a DIR/Floortime perspective. Ensure the summary is concise and adheres to DIR/Floortime terminology. Organise the summary under the following headings.)

**Client Presentation and Context:**

[Describe the client's presenting concerns, current emotional state, and regulation status at the start of the session. Note any relevant changes since the last session in terms of behaviour, mood, or developmental progress. Describe any significant life events or contextual factors affecting the client's presentation. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Caregiver/Parent Participation and Observations:**

[Describe the level and quality of caregiver/parent involvement during the session. Note any observations, concerns, or insights shared by the caregiver about the client's functioning between sessions. Detail any caregiver-client interactions observed during the session and the quality of their attunement. (Only include if caregiver was present or if mentioned in the transcript, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Individual Differences Profile:**

[Detail the client's sensory processing patterns observed during the session, including sensory-seeking or sensory-avoiding behaviours. Note any motor planning challenges, visual-spatial processing patterns, auditory processing observations, and other relevant processing differences. Describe how these individual differences were accommodated during the session. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Current Functional Emotional Developmental Capacities (FEDCs):**

[Assess and describe the client's functioning across the six core functional emotional developmental capacities, also known as FEDCs, observed during this session. Use the following framework, noting which capacities were demonstrated, emerging, or challenged. Only include capacities that were relevant to this session:]

**FEDC 1** \- Self\-Regulation and Interest in the World: \[Describe the client's ability to regulate their emotional and sensory state\, and their interest in engaging with the world around them\. Note whether the client was able to achieve and maintain a calm\, alert\, focused state\. \(Only include if relevant to the session\.\)\]

**FEDC 2** \- Engagement and Relating: \[Describe the quality of emotional engagement and connection between the client and therapist/caregiver\. Note warmth\, affection\, intimacy\, and the "gleam in the eye" that indicates emotional connection\. \(Only include if relevant to the session\.\)\]

**FEDC 3** \- Two\-Way Purposeful Communication: \[Describe the client's ability to open and close circles of communication through gestures\, vocalisations\, or other intentional signals\. Note the number and complexity of circles achieved and whether communication was initiated by the client\, or therapist or caregiver\. \(Only include if relevant to the session\.\)\]

**FEDC 4** \- Complex Communication and Shared Problem\-Solving: \[Describe the client's ability to engage in longer chains of back\-and\-forth communication \(continuous flow\) and to problem\-solve collaboratively\. Note the number of consecutive circles of communication achieved and the complexity of problem\-solving interactions\. \(Only include if relevant to the session\.\)\]

**FEDC 5** \- Using Symbols and Creating Emotional Ideas: \[Describe any pretend play\, use of words or symbols to represent ideas\, and the client's ability to express emotional ideas\. Note the themes explored in symbolic play\. \(Only include if relevant to the session\.\)\]

**FEDC 6** \- Logical Thinking and Building Bridges Between Ideas: \[Describe the client's ability to connect ideas logically\, answer "why" questions\, and think abstractly\. Note any cause\-and\-effect reasoning or logical connections made\. \(Only include if relevant to the session\.\)\]

**Play-Based Activities and Interactions:**

[Describe the specific play activities engaged in during the session. Detail how the therapist followed the client's lead and built upon the client's natural interests and motivations. Note the types of play materials used and how they facilitated interaction. Describe any symbolic or pretend play themes that emerged.]

**Floortime Techniques and Strategies Used:**

[Detail the specific DIR/Floortime techniques employed during the session. Use bullet points for clarity:]

<br>
* [**Following the child's lead:** Describe how the therapist joined the client's activity and built upon their interests. (Only include if used in session.)]


* [**Circles of communication:** Describe strategies used to open and close circles and extend interaction sequences. Include approximate count of circles achieved in key interactions. (Only include if used in session.)]


* [**Playful obstruction:** Describe any playful obstacles or challenges introduced to extend communication and problem-solving. (Only include if used in session.)]


* [**Affect and animation:** Describe how the therapist used vocal tone, facial expressions, and energy level to engage the client. (Only include if used in session.)]


* [**Expanding the range:** Describe efforts to broaden emotional or thematic range during play. (Only include if used in session.)]


* [**Other techniques:** Note any additional DIR/Floortime strategies used. (Only include if used in session.)]


<br>
Child's Response and Engagement:

[Describe the client's level of engagement throughout the session, including any shifts in regulation, attention, or interaction quality. Note moments of particular connection or breakthrough, including any "aha moments" or increased initiation from the client. Describe any challenges to engagement and how these were addressed. Detail the client's emotional expression and range during the session. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Therapeutic Relationship and Co-Regulation:**

[Describe the quality of the therapeutic relationship and attunement between therapist and client. Note how the therapist supported the client's regulation through co-regulation. Describe the emotional warmth, trust, and safety established during the session. Comment on any challenges in building rapport or maintaining connection. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Progress:**

[Summarise progress toward established therapeutic goals, with specific reference to movement through the FEDCs. Highlight any notable developmental gains or emerging capacities. Note any areas where progress has stalled or new challenges have emerged. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Home Practice and Caregiver Coaching:**

[Describe any suggestions or guidance provided to caregivers for implementing Floortime principles at home. Note specific activities or strategies recommended for daily interactions. Include any caregiver questions or concerns addressed. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.)]

**Plan for Next Session:**

[Outline the focus for the next session, including which FEDCs will be targeted and what types of activities might be explored. Note any materials or preparations needed. Include the time, date, and day of the next scheduled session if mentioned. (Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript, contextual notes, or clinical note, otherwise leave blank.)]

**Session Summary:**

[Provide a brief recap of the session in less than four sentences, highlighting the client's engagement level, key developmental capacities addressed, notable moments of connection or progress, and overall session quality.]

