### Young DIVA-5 Questionnaire

### Part 1: Symptoms of Attention-Deficit

### DSM-5-TR Criteria A1

#### <u>Inattention – six or more of the following are required</u>

#### A

\[Describe if the child often fails to give close attention to details or makes careless mistakes in schoolwork, at work, or during other activities (e.g., overlooks or misses details, work is inaccurate). If applicable, provide relevant real-life examples from the transcript. If no information about this diagnostic criterion is found in the transcript or contextual notes, print “Information related to this diagnostic criterion not found in the transcript.”]

#### B

\[Describe if the child often has difficulty sustaining attention in tasks or play activities (e.g., has difficulty remaining focused during lectures, conversations, or lengthy reading). If applicable, provide relevant real-life examples from the transcript. If no information about this diagnostic criterion is found in the transcript or contextual notes, print “Information related to this diagnostic criterion not found in the transcript.”]

#### C

\[Describe if the child often does not seem to listen when spoken to directly (e.g., mind seems elsewhere, even in the absence of any obvious distraction). If applicable, provide relevant real-life examples from the transcript. If no information about this diagnostic criterion is found in the transcript or contextual notes, print “Information related to this diagnostic criterion not found in the transcript.”]

#### D

\[Describe if the child often does not follow through on instructions and fails to finish schoolwork, chores, or duties in the workplace (e.g., starts tasks but quickly loses focus and is easily sidetracked). If applicable, provide relevant real-life examples from the transcript. If no information about this diagnostic criterion is found in the transcript or contextual notes, print “Information related to this diagnostic criterion not found in the transcript.”]

#### E

\[Describe if the child often has difficulty organising tasks and activities (e.g., difficulty managing sequential tasks; difficulty keeping materials and belongings in order; messy, disorganised work; has poor time management; fails to meet deadlines). If applicable, provide relevant real-life examples from the transcript. If no information about this diagnostic criterion is found in the transcript or contextual notes, print “Information related to this diagnostic criterion not found in the transcript.”]

#### F

