(Generate a brief professional letter to a busy referring doctor from the treating psychologist or mental health clinician. The letter concisely summarises the client’s episode of care, based on the client’s notes, contextual notes, psychometric assessment results, and transcript data. The letter must concisely summarise only relevant clinical information, such as any assessments carried out on the client, treatment provided, and recommendations on future management. Limit to 1-1.5 pages or approximately 300-500 words. The language used must be formal and reflect evidence-based medicine and mental health care. If a client’s name is not mentioned in the transcript, notes or contextual notes, refer to them as “client” - do not invent any names. Use the letter format layout below:)

<br>
Re: [Print the client’s first and last name. If unknown, leave blank.]

DOB: [Print the client’s date of birth in DD/MM/YYYY format. If unknown, leave blank.]

Dear Dr [Referring Clinician's Name (use appropriate title if applicable, if the addressee’s name is not known, simply address as “Dear Dr”)],

"Thank you for referring [Client’s Full Name (only include if mentioned in the transcript, notes or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)] to me."

[Provide a brief summary of the most important, clinically relevant findings about the patient’s circumstances, diagnosis and information from the sessions. Do not include detailed session content, only a brief summary focusing on the most relevant clinical details only. Using the client’s session notes, transcripts, and contextual notes during the specified treatment period, include information such as the client’s presenting issues, symptoms, the client's goals for treatment, and other key client information only if relevant to their presentation and therapy. If applicable, describe how any of this information has significantly changed during the treatment period.] (Only include information that is explicitly mentioned in the transcripts, notes, or contextual notes.)

[Provide a brief summary of the treatment provided by the clinician. Using the client’s session notes, transcripts, and contextual summaries, include information such as: how many sessions have been completed to date; frequency of sessions; modality of therapy (e.g., CBT, ACT, schema therapy, psychodynamic psychotherapy); types of interventions used; types of homework or other activities completed as part of treatment; success or otherwise of treatment; the client’s engagement in treatment; and the client’s rapport or therapeutic alliance with the clinician.] (Do not include detailed session content, only a brief summary with the most important findings and information. Only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript(s), note(s) or contextual note(s), otherwise leave blank.)

Psychometric Assessment Results (only include section if psychometric results are present):

* [Using bullet points, list the name of each psychometric assessment. For each assessment, you must include: 1) Assessment name, 2) One sentence description explaining what the tool measures (e.g, "The Depression Anxiety Stress Scale measures the severity of depressive symptoms over the past week"), 3) Results summary including the first paragraph of each assessment verbatim, and 4) Full quantitative results (scores, percentiles, clinical ranges). If the same assessment has been administered on more than one occasion, only list the most recent and include any change in symptoms over time. List assessment results from most recently completed. (Only include information that is explicitly in the client’s psychometric assessments results if available, otherwise leave blank.) If no psychometric assessments were administered, do not include this section).]

[Provide a brief summary of the plan moving forward or future treatment directions between the clinician and the client. If applicable, include a brief outline of any risk to safety posed by the client, including protective factors that mitigate the risk. Provide any recommendations for future treatment and management mentioned by the clinician that may involve other health professionals or other health services. Provide the rationale for each of these recommendations. Include any request that the clinician has made for the treating doctor and the reasons provided for this request. (Only include information that is explicitly mentioned in the client’s notes, transcripts, and contextual summaries.)]

[If the client requires a new referral to continue treatment or review of the Mental Health Treatment Plan, request that the referring doctor provide a new referral so the patient can continue to engage in psychological therapy] (be brief, only include if explicitly mentioned in the transcript(s), note(s) or contextual notes)

"Should you have any further questions regarding [Client's first and last Name (only include if mentioned in the transcript, notes or contextual notes, otherwise leave blank)], please do not hesitate to contact me."

Sincerely,
[Clinician Name]
[Clinician Profession]
[Practice Name]

