### Description

A Wellbeing Plan (ACC8541) is completed by clinicians in collaboration with the kiritaki (client) when planning their recovery from a covered mental injury within New Zealand's ACC. This form is used either when a kiritaki has not previously had a Wellbeing Plan for their injuries, or when a kiritaki is returning for treatment on an existing covered claim and requires a new Wellbeing Plan. This template synthesises information from NovoNote and NovoPsych to assist clinicians in drafting a Wellbeing Plan.

### Prompt

