## SMART Goals for Clients

**ID:** 15307  
**Type IDs:** 6  
**Category IDs:** 1,3,4  

### Description

Document SMART goals and provide them to clients. This template focuses on helping the clinician and client record SMART goals i.e., goals that are Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, and Time-bound. Can also be used to track the client’s progress in achieving those goals.

### Prompt

(The template below will summarise a section of a session where a clinician and client have discussed the client’s goals. Output will focus only on those aspects of the session that deal with setting and/or achieving goals. Your output will not cover any other aspect of the session that is not relevant to the client’s goals. A discussion about goals between a clinician and a client may be a highly structured approach or a less structured, more casual approach. Goal-setting sessions may be the first session between a mental health clinician and a client or a follow-up session where a client may modify their goals, set new goals, or review progress against goals. You will decide what type of conversation is being had about goals in this session: is it goal-setting, goal-modifying, goal-tracking, or a combination of these. Your analysis of the goals discussed must follow the SMART approach towards setting goals: Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, and Time-bound. This document is designed to record client goals and will be provided to the client. Therefore, you must provide your output in the first person, referring to the client by name, and using terms such as "you" or "your" rather than referring to them as "the client" or "the patient" in the third person. Write in an encouraging yet concrete manner. Organise your summary using the following format:)

### SMART GOALS - [Print client’s first and last name]

[Print the session date in Day Month, Year format]

Dear [client first name],

Thank you for discussing your goals with me. This document uses the SMART Goal framework to clearly define what you hope to achieve.

🥇 **GOAL 1:** [Goal Title]

[Paraphrase the goal as articulated by the client and clinician during the session. Capture the essence of what the client wants to achieve, including any context about why this goal matters to them.]

🧠 SMART Summary:

| SMART | Status | Description |
| ----- | ------ | ----------- |
| Specific<br>🎯 | [Insert 🟢 if the goal meets criterion, insert 🔴 if the goal does not meet criterion, or insert 🟠 if the goal only partially meets criterion.] | [Define the specific element of the goal, as described in session. If the goal is only partially specific, state why it is only partially specific and encourage the client to be even more specific. If the goal is not specific at all, print “Please describe the goal in more specific terms.” For goals that are partially met or not met at all, provide a suggestion in the form of a question about how the client can make their goal more specific.] |
| Measurable<br>📏 | [Insert 🟢 if the goal meets criterion, insert 🔴 if the goal does not meet criterion, or insert 🟠 if the goal only partially meets criterion.] | [Define the measurable element of the goal, as described in session. If the goal is only partially measurable, state why it is only partially measurable and encourage the client to be even more measurable. If the goal is not measurable at all, print "Please describe the goal in more measurable terms." For goals that are partially met or not met at all, provide a suggestion in the form of a question about how the client can make their goal more measurable.] |
| Achievable<br>🏆 | [Insert 🟢 if the goal meets criterion, insert 🔴 if the goal does not meet criterion, or insert 🟠 if the goal only partially meets criterion.] | [Define the achievable element of the goal, as described in session. If the goal is only partially achievable, state why it is only partially achievable and encourage the client to be even more achievable. If the goal is not achievable at all, print "Please describe the goal in more achievable terms." For goals that are partially met or not met at all, provide a suggestion in the form of a question about how the client can make their goal more achievable.] |
| Relevant<br>💡 | [Insert 🟢 if the goal meets criterion, insert 🔴 if the goal does not meet criterion, or insert 🟠 if the goal only partially meets criterion.] | [Define the relevant element of the goal, as described in session. If the goal is only partially relevant, state why it is only partially relevant and encourage the client to be even more relevant. If the goal is not relevant at all, print "Please describe the goal in more relevant terms." For goals that are partially met or not met at all, provide a suggestion in the form of a question about how the client can make their goal more relevant.] |
| Time-Bound<br>⌚ | [Insert 🟢 if the goal meets criterion, insert 🔴 if the goal does not meet criterion, or insert 🟠 if the goal only partially meets criterion.] | [Define the time-bound element of the goal, as described in session. If the goal is only partially time-bound, state why it is only partially time-bound and encourage the client to be even more time-bound. If the goal is not time-bound at all, print "Please describe the goal in more time-bound terms." For goals that are partially met or not met at all, provide a suggestion in the form of a question about how the client can make their goal more time-bound.] |

📢 Action Steps:

[List concrete actions or steps that can be taken to move towards the goal. If no concrete steps were discussed, write “Please list your next steps towards this goal”.]

🧱 Anticipated Barriers And Obstacles:

[Describe barriers that might get in the way of achieving the goal. This may include external obstacles in the world, or internal obstacles such as habits or lack of motivation. If not explicitly discussed in the transcript, leave blank and do not print sub-heading.]

✨ Strategies To Overcome Obstacles:

[Describe ways of overcoming barriers or obstacles to achieving the goal. What skills, strategies, mindsets, habits were discussed. Describe in detail. If not explicitly discussed in the transcript, leave blank and do not print heading.]

📖 Progress Review

[Summarise what the client and clinician discussed regarding current progress on this goal. Include specific examples, achievements, challenges, setbacks, or barriers mentioned. Write in an affirming and congratulatory way if the client is on track with their goal. If the client is not on track, be realistic and consider reframing the failure in an encouraging and compassionate way. Describe the current status of the client’s progress with achieving this goal by using terms such as “On track” / “Partially achieved” / “Achieved” / “Modified” / “Discontinued” / “Experiencing barriers”. Note if and how the goal was adjusted, refined, or replaced with a new goal. If there is no explicit mention of the client’s current progress with this goal, leave blank and do not print the sub-heading.]

🥇 **GOAL 2:** [Goal Title/Brief Description]

[Repeat the same structure as Goal 1 as many times as necessary for each additional goal that was discussed.]

***

<br>


